cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the message-error rate and threshold of LDPC codes, which are important topics in information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the optimization of protograph LDPC codes, which involves computational complexity. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - LDPC codes are commonly used in communication systems, which fall under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the structure of protograph LDPC codes, which can be analyzed using network theory. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the construction of LDPC codes, which involves the design and implementation of algorithms.
